subject: Golf
lead_paragraph: Annika Sorenstam nearly holed her third shot on the par-5 18th, then lipped out a 9-foot birdie try to give Angela Stanford a one-stroke victory in the inaugural Lorena Ochoa Invitational in Guadalajara, Mexico. Sorenstam shot a 69 and finished her next-to-last L.P.G.A. Tour event tied for second. Stanford also finished with a 69.
